The WitnessPolice are appealing to anyone with information on the whereabouts of Xolani Brian Ndlovu (32) to contact investigating officer Warrant Officer Mdunge of Nottingham SAPS on 082 368 8217 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pietermaritzburg - Nottingham Road police are appealing for assistance from the public in finding a suspect in connection to the Solik murders. Christine (57) and Roger (66) Solik were attacked and kidnapped from their home at The Bend estate near Nottingham Road last month during a home invasion attack. Christine&rsquo;s body was found later that day in the Lotheni River in Impendle, her feet and hands bound with wire and her face covered with a pillow case.Roger&rsquo;s body was found three days later by the Pietermaritzburg police&rsquo;s search and rescue team. He was found lodged between rocks in the same river, a few kilometres from where his wife was found.Police spokesperson Nqobile Gwala said they are looking for Xolani Brian Ndlovu (32). Ndlovu is wanted for two counts of murder, house robbery, kidnapping and stealing a car.Gwala said they do not know where Ndlovu stays, but said he is often seen at Umlazi C and F section; Mpophomeni; Mafakatini and France in Pietermaritzburg.Gwala said Ndlovu is 1,75 metres in height, fair in complexion and well built. One of the suspects, Thulani Mthembu (43), was arrested earlier this month for the murders, appeared at the Howick Magistrate&rsquo;s Court and was remanded in custody until next Wednesday for a bail application. Gwala appealed to anyone with information on the whereabouts of Ndlovu to contact investigating officer Warrant Officer Mdunge of Nottingham Road SAPS on 082 368 8217 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.